{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_54","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' /root/new-ralph-burning/multibackend-orchestration/.ralph/projects/implement-an-event-driven-multi-turn-prd/loops/001-interactive-prd-state-machine-foundation/20260222041049-spec.md\"","aggregated_output":"---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 1\nproject: implement-an-event-driven-multi-turn-prd\nbackend: claude(opus)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-02-22T04:10:49Z\n---\n\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. This is loop 7, first planning phase, with zero completed loops. The entire interactive PRD feature needs to be built. \n\nThe natural first feature to implement is the **foundational layer**: the state machine types, persistence, configuration fields, error variants, and module scaffolding. This creates the substrate that all subsequent features (question generation, draft generation, feedback loops, runtime integration, tests) will build upon.\n\n# Feature: Interactive PRD State Machine Foundation\n\n## Description\nEstablish the foundational types, persistence layer, configuration fields, error variants, and module structure for the event-driven interactive PRD workflow. This includes the `PrdWorkflowState` enum, `InteractivePrdState` persistence struct with atomic JSON save/load, new `WorkspaceConfig` fields with validation, PRD lifecycle label constants, the `interactive_prd` module export in the daemon, an error variant in `RalphError`, and an approval-detection helper. This feature does **not** include runtime integration or GitHub API calls — it purely defines the data model, config surface, and core helpers that all subsequent features will depend on.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] New file `src/daemon/interactive_prd.rs` exists with module-level doc comment.\n- [ ] `PrdWorkflowState` enum with variants `Pending`, `AwaitingAnswers`, `AwaitingFeedback`, `Done`, `Failed` — derives `Serialize`, `Deserialize`, `Debug`, `Clone`, `PartialEq`, `Eq`.\n- [ ] `InteractivePrdState` struct with all minimum persisted fields from the prompt: `issue_number`, `owner`, `repo`, `state`, `question_revision`, `draft_revision`, `questions_comment_id`, `questions_posted_at`, `latest_draft_comment_id`, `latest_draft_body`, `user_answers`, `last_processed_comment_id`, `error_count`, `last_error`, `last_advanced_at`.\n- [ ] `InteractivePrdState::new(owner, repo, issue_number)` constructor initializes to `Pending` with zeroed counters and `None` optionals.\n- [ ] `InteractivePrdState::save(data_dir)` writes atomically (temp file + rename) to `{data_dir}/{owner}/{repo}/.ralph/interactive-prd/{issue_number}.json`, creating parent dirs as needed.\n- [ ] `InteractivePrdState::load(data_dir, owner, repo, issue_number)` reads from the same path, returning `Ok(None)` if file does not exist.\n- [ ] `InteractivePrdState::is_terminal()` returns `true` for `Done` and `Failed`.\n- [ ] Approval detection helper function `detect_approval(text: &str) -> bool` that strips fenced code blocks and inline code, checks negative phrases first, then positive phrases with word boundaries (case-insensitive), returns `false` if both positive and negative are present.\n- [ ] Comment marker helper `prd_marker(issue_number: u32, kind: &str, version: u32) -> String` producing `<!-- ralph:prd:{issue_number}:{kind}-v{version} -->`.\n- [ ] PRD lifecycle label constants: `PRD_LABELS` array containing `ralph:prd`, `ralph:prd-active`, `ralph:prd-approved`, `ralph:prd-done`, `ralph:prd-failed` with colors and descriptions (matching the pattern in `github.rs` for `REQUIRED_LABELS`).\n- [ ] `WorkspaceConfig` gains six new fields: `daemon_prd_enabled` (default `true`), `daemon_prd_question_backends` (default `[\"claude\", \"codex\"]`), `daemon_prd_writer_backend` (default `\"claude\"`), `daemon_prd_reviewer_backend` (default `\"codex\"`), `daemon_prd_max_revisions` (default `3`), `daemon_prd_backend_timeout_secs` (default `120`).\n- [ ] Config validation: `daemon_prd_question_backends` must contain exactly 2 elements; all backend specs must parse with the existing backend spec parser; invalid config returns a clear `Validation` error.\n- [ ] `RalphError` gains variant `InteractivePrdFailed(String)` with exit code 14.\n- [ ] `src/daemon/mod.rs` exports `pub mod interactive_prd;`.\n- [ ] Unit tests in `interactive_prd.rs` (`#[cfg(test)] mod tests`): state serialization round-trip for all 5 states, approval detection positive/negative/edge cases (including code-block stripping, mixed signals, word boundaries), marker generation, `is_terminal()`, save/load round-trip using `tempdir`.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `src/daemon/interactive_prd.rs` — **Create**: `PrdWorkflowState` enum, `InteractivePrdState` struct, `new()`, `save()`, `load()`, `is_terminal()`, `detect_approval()`, `prd_marker()`, `PRD_LIFECYCLE_LABELS` constant, unit tests.\n- `src/daemon/mod.rs` — **Modify**: add `pub mod interactive_prd;` export.\n- `src/config/global.rs` — **Modify**: add 6 new `daemon_prd_*` fields to `WorkspaceConfig` with `#[serde(default)]` and defaults, add validation logic in the existing config validation function.\n- `src/error.rs` — **Modify**: add `InteractivePrdFailed(String)` variant, map it to exit code 14.\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: none (this is the foundational feature)\n- Blocks: GitHub comment fetching helpers, question generation transition, draft generation transition, feedback/revision loop, approval/done transition, failure handling, runtime integration, conformance tests\n\n---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
