{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_67","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' tests/unit/flow_semantics_test.rs\"","aggregated_output":"use ralph_burning::contexts::workflow_composition::{flow_semantics, stage_plan_for_flow};\nuse ralph_burning::shared::domain::{FlowPreset, StageId};\n\n#[test]\nfn standard_flow_semantics_match_spec() {\n    let semantics = flow_semantics(FlowPreset::Standard);\n\n    assert_eq!(semantics.planning_stage, StageId::Planning);\n    assert_eq!(semantics.execution_stage, StageId::Implementation);\n    assert_eq!(\n        semantics.remediation_trigger_stages,\n        &[StageId::Qa, StageId::Review]\n    );\n    assert_eq!(\n        semantics.late_stages,\n        &[\n            StageId::CompletionPanel,\n            StageId::AcceptanceQa,\n            StageId::FinalReview,\n        ]\n    );\n    assert_eq!(semantics.prompt_review_stage, Some(StageId::PromptReview));\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn quick_dev_flow_semantics_are_defined() {\n    let semantics = flow_semantics(FlowPreset::QuickDev);\n\n    assert_eq!(semantics.planning_stage, StageId::PlanAndImplement);\n    assert_eq!(semantics.execution_stage, StageId::ApplyFixes);\n    assert_eq!(semantics.remediation_trigger_stages, &[StageId::Review]);\n    assert_eq!(semantics.late_stages, &[StageId::FinalReview]);\n    assert_eq!(semantics.prompt_review_stage, None);\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn docs_change_flow_semantics_match_spec() {\n    let semantics = flow_semantics(FlowPreset::DocsChange);\n\n    assert_eq!(semantics.planning_stage, StageId::DocsPlan);\n    assert_eq!(semantics.execution_stage, StageId::DocsUpdate);\n    assert_eq!(\n        semantics.remediation_trigger_stages,\n        &[StageId::DocsValidation, StageId::Review]\n    );\n    assert!(semantics.late_stages.is_empty());\n    assert_eq!(semantics.prompt_review_stage, None);\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn ci_improvement_flow_semantics_match_spec() {\n    let semantics = flow_semantics(FlowPreset::CiImprovement);\n\n    assert_eq!(semantics.planning_stage, StageId::CiPlan);\n    assert_eq!(semantics.execution_stage, StageId::CiUpdate);\n    assert_eq!(\n        semantics.remediation_trigger_stages,\n        &[StageId::CiValidation, StageId::Review]\n    );\n    assert!(semantics.late_stages.is_empty());\n    assert_eq!(semantics.prompt_review_stage, None);\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn standard_stage_plan_for_flow_honors_prompt_review_toggle() {\n    assert_eq!(\n        stage_plan_for_flow(FlowPreset::Standard, true),\n        vec![\n            StageId::PromptReview,\n            StageId::Planning,\n            StageId::Implementation,\n            StageId::Qa,\n            StageId::Review,\n            StageId::CompletionPanel,\n            StageId::AcceptanceQa,\n            StageId::FinalReview,\n        ]\n    );\n    assert_eq!(\n        stage_plan_for_flow(FlowPreset::Standard, false),\n        vec![\n            StageId::Planning,\n            StageId::Implementation,\n            StageId::Qa,\n            StageId::Review,\n            StageId::CompletionPanel,\n            StageId::AcceptanceQa,\n            StageId::FinalReview,\n        ]\n    );\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn non_standard_stage_plans_ignore_prompt_review_toggle() {\n    assert_eq!(\n        stage_plan_for_flow(FlowPreset::DocsChange, true),\n        stage_plan_for_flow(FlowPreset::DocsChange, false)\n    );\n    assert_eq!(\n        stage_plan_for_flow(FlowPreset::CiImprovement, true),\n        stage_plan_for_flow(FlowPreset::CiImprovement, false)\n    );\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_68","type":"agent_message","text":"# Feature: Requirements Drafting and Project Seed Handoff\n\n## Description\nLoops 1 through 9 already delivered the rewrite foundation: workspace init and flow discovery, stage contracts and renderers, effective config and active project resolution, canonical project/run storage and queries, agent execution, standard-flow orchestration, retry/resume semantics, completion rounds and amendments, and docs/CI flow execution. Git checkpoint history stops at loop 9 planning, and the entire `requirements` bounded context plus all four `requirements` CLI commands are still stubs at `HEAD`. The next missing roadmap slice is a canonical requirements-run workflow under `.ralph-burning/requirements/` that can draft requirements from an idea, pause for clarifying answers when needed, and emit a durable project-seed handoff without auto-creating a project or touching legacy `.ralph` PRD state.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Introduce a `RequirementsRun` state model persisted at `.ralph-burning/requirements/<run-id>/run.json` with, at minimum, `run_id`, `idea`, `mode` (`draft` or `quick`), `status` (`drafting`, `awaiting_answers`, `completed`, `failed`), `question_round`, `latest_question_set_id`, `latest_draft_id`, `latest_review_id`, `latest_seed_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, and `status_summary`.\n- [ ] Each requirements run also persists `journal.ndjson`, `answers.toml`, `answers.json`, `history/payloads/*`, `history/artifacts/*`, `seed/project.json`, `seed/prompt.md`, and `runtime/{logs,backend}/*` under `.ralph-burning/requirements/<run-id>/`.\n- [ ] `requirements show <run-id>` derives its read model from `run.json` and `journal.ndjson`, not by scanning artifacts, and prints the run ID, mode, status, question round, last failure summary if present, pending question count, recommended flow, and the seed prompt path when complete.\n- [ ] Define structured contracts and deterministic renderers for four requirements-stage outputs: `question_set`, `requirements_draft`, `requirements_review`, and `project_seed`.\n- [ ] Requirements contract validation follows the same invariant as project stages: schema validation occurs before any state mutation, domain validation occurs after schema validation and before transition commit, and rendered Markdown is never parsed for control flow.\n- [ ] `question_set` payloads include stable question IDs, prompt text, rationale, `required` flag, and optional suggested defaults; those IDs are the only keys accepted in `answers.toml` and persisted `answers.json`.\n- [ ] `requirements_draft` payloads include a problem summary, goals, non-goals, constraints, acceptance criteria, risks or open questions, and a recommended flow constrained to the built-in presets only: `standard`, `quick_dev`, `docs_change`, or `ci_improvement`.\n- [ ] `project_seed` payloads include a recommended project `id`, project `name`, built-in `flow`, a final `prompt.md` body, and a short handoff summary suitable for manual `project create --prompt`.\n- [ ] `requirements draft --idea \"<text>\"` creates a new run, durably records the idea, invokes question generation, and either transitions to `awaiting_answers` after committing the question payload/artifact plus an editable `answers.toml` template, or continues directly into draft/review/seed generation when no questions are required.\n- [ ] `requirements quick --idea \"<text>\"` creates a new run in `quick` mode, skips question generation entirely, and executes draft -> review -> seed generation in one command using the same persistence and validation rules.\n- [ ] `requirements answer <run-id>` is valid for runs in `awaiting_answers` and for failed runs whose latest durable boundary is a committed question set; it opens `<run-dir>/answers.toml` in `$EDITOR`, validates that every required question has a non-empty answer, persists `answers.json`, and resumes from the answers boundary instead of creating a new run.\n- [ ] If `$EDITOR` fails or exits non-zero during `requirements answer`, the run state, journal, and previously accepted answers remain unchanged.\n- [ ] Requirements drafting reuses `agent_execution`, but `agent_execution` must be generalized from workflow-only `StageContract` usage to a domain-neutral structured-contract interface so requirements contracts do not have to be added to the project workflow `StageId` enum.\n- [ ] Planner defaults drive question generation, drafting, and project-seed generation; reviewer defaults drive requirements review; existing workspace default backend/model resolution and raw-output persistence rules continue to apply.\n- [ ] Review outcomes have distinct semantics: `approved` allows seed generation and completion; `conditionally_approved` still completes but records follow-ups in canonical seed metadata and the rendered handoff summary; `request_changes` and `rejected` fail the run after the review payload/artifact are durably committed and before any seed files become visible.\n- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if the question payload/artifact pair fails to persist, the run must not transition to `awaiting_answers` and no partial question/template files may remain visible.\n- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if answer validation fails, `answers.json` is not replaced, no draft/review/seed stage runs, and the run remains at the same committed question boundary.\n- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if the draft or review payload/artifact pair fails to persist, the corresponding journal success event is not appended and no downstream stage begins.\n- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if `seed/project.json` is written but `seed/prompt.md` fails, both seed outputs are removed, the run remains non-completed, and only the already committed draft/review history survives.\n- [ ] Completed requirements runs are immutable, failed runs retain the latest committed question set, answers, draft, and review artifacts, and `question_round` is monotonic across repeated answer cycles.\n- [ ] `requirements show <run-id>` prints a suggested `ralph-burning project create --id ... --name ... --flow ... --prompt <seed/prompt.md>` command assembled from `seed/project.json` and `seed/prompt.md`.\n- [ ] This loop does not auto-create, mutate, select, or delete projects; project handoff is durable seed output only, leaving `project create` as an explicit user action.\n- [ ] Public behavior is covered by new Gherkin scenarios for: draft requiring answers, draft with no questions, quick-mode happy path, editor failure, answer validation failure, conditional approval handoff, review request_changes failure, and seed-write rollback.\n- [ ] Existing workspace, project, and run behavior remains unchanged, including the current quick_dev run-execution deferral outside the `requirements` command surface.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/mod.rs` - replace the placeholder with module exports and public entrypoints for the requirements lifecycle\n- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/model.rs` - add requirements run IDs, status enums, journal event types, pointers to latest payloads, and seed metadata\n- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs` - define domain-neutral contracts for `question_set`, `requirements_draft`, `requirements_review`, and `project_seed`\n- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/renderers.rs` - render deterministic `questions.md`, `requirements.md`, `review.md`, and seed handoff artifacts\n- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs` - orchestrate `draft`, `quick`, `show`, and `answer`, including answer-template validation and seed rollback rules\n- `src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs` - generalize invocation metadata away from workflow-only `StageContract` coupling\n- `src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs` - support domain-neutral contract evaluation while preserving existing workflow behavior\n- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - adapt existing workflow stage contracts to the generalized agent-execution contract interface\n- `src/adapters/fs.rs` - add filesystem stores for requirements runs, journals, answer files, payload/artifact history, runtime diagnostics, and atomic seed-pair writes\n- `src/adapters/stub_backend.rs` - add deterministic requirements-stage payloads for tests\n- `src/cli/requirements.rs` - implement all four requirements commands and the editor-driven answer flow\n- `src/shared/error.rs` - add invalid requirements state, answer validation, and seed persistence error variants\n- `tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature` - add public requirements-drafting scenarios\n- `tests/unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs` - add domain and service tests for the requirements state machine and failure invariants\n- `tests/cli.rs` - add end-to-end CLI coverage for `requirements draft`, `requirements quick`, `requirements show`, and `requirements answer`\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 9 (Docs Change and CI Improvement Flow Execution)\n- Blocks: Loop 11 (Daemon routing, tasks, leases, watchers, rebase, and interactive requirements path)\n\n---"}}
